{
  "texts": [
    "Voters mirrored these concerns.",
    "The 2024 Digital News Report by the Reuters Institute for the Study of Journalism found that 81% of South Africa's news consumers were worried about correct versus false news on the internet [22].",
    "In 2023, aYouGov survey revealed that most adult US citizens were concerned about the spread of AI deepfakes and political propaganda [23].",
    "In the UK in 2023, Ofcom, the regulatory and competition authority for broadcasting and telecommunications, found that over half (58%)of surveyed internet users were concerned about GenAI's future impact on society [24].",
    "In a survey fielded in the USA in the autumn of 2024 by the Pew Research Center, nearly eight times as many respondents expected AI to be used for mostly bad purposes in the 2024 US presidential election, versus those who thought it would be used mostly for good [25].Commentators around the world referred to the elections in 2024 as the \"AI elections\"usually expressing implicit or explicit fear when they used this term [26], [27], [28], [29]."
  ]
}